equals zero, then the rate

00:04:57.420 --> 00:05:02.610
constant equals factor A. What
would be true about the

00:05:02.610 --> 00:05:08.390
temperature for 1 over
temperature to equal zero?

00:05:08.390 --> 00:05:09.930
Very big.

00:05:09.930 --> 00:05:14.920
So, at the biggest, hugest
temperature you can imagine,

00:05:14.920 --> 00:05:18.420
the rate constant's going to
equal A. And so, factor A

00:05:18.420 --> 00:05:21.780
depends on the nature of the
material being studied and you

00:05:21.780 --> 00:05:24.540
would have to determine
what that value is.

00:05:24.540 --> 00:05:26.370
But it's definitely not
temperature dependent.

00:05:26.370 --> 00:05:29.880
It's the value of the rate
constant at an enormous

00:05:29.880 --> 00:05:33.480
temperature.

00:05:33.480 --> 00:05:36.060
So, what about activation
energy?

00:05:36.060 --> 00:05:38.190
Do you think that's temperature
dependent?

00:05:38.190 --> 00:05:39.490
Why don't you tell me
