00:07:43.110 --> 00:07:46.580
So the activation energy is
not temperature dependent.

00:07:46.580 --> 00:07:49.980
You can calculate what the
activation energy is by

00:07:49.980 --> 00:07:53.430
plotting the rate constants
versus 1 over temperature, and

00:07:53.430 --> 00:07:56.790
then you get it from the
